{
  "texts": [
    "We compare our network (with 340 neurons in the hidden layer) with published networks containing 340 or more neurons in the hidden layer.",
    "The test accuracy of our model is higher than that of all other SNNs (see Table 1).",
    "Moreover, we tested a 16-layer fully connected SNN (16FC), a 5-layer ConvNet SNN (LeNet5), and a 16-layer ConvNet SNN (VGG16).",
    "For deeper networks, we noticed that, even though the SNN and ReLU network are initialized with the same parameters, sometimes they exhibit different performance after several epochs due to numerical instabilities.",
    "For this reason, in all cases where the number of hidden layers is larger than one we report the average performance across 16 learning trials with different random initial conditions."
  ]
}